news.title: Eco-sensitive zones’ master plan set, government can draft CZMP: Goa CM
news.para: Chief Minister Pramod Sawant announced the readiness of the zonal master plan for eco-sensitive zones and the permission received for drafting the CZMP 2019, which could benefit structures near the high tide line. MLAs urged for CZMP finalization to aid coastal communities.

news.title: Income tax department flags gaps in reporting of property sales
news.para: The income tax department is seeing a rise in tax evasion petitions related to undisclosed property deals. Officials suspect underreporting by land registrar offices, particularly a mismatch at the Hingna sub-registrar's office, is enabling tax evasion. This gap in reporting allows sellers to avoid capital gains tax by omitting property sales from their tax returns.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body facing backlog of unresolved e-khata grievances
news.para: Bruhat Bengaluru Mahanagara Palike is dealing with many e-khata complaints. Several wards have a high number of unresolved cases. Many citizens are not happy with the initial resolutions. Mahadevapura zone has the most unresolved cases. BBMP urges citizens to use the e-khata helpline. The helpline handles many calls daily. BBMP claims a high disposal rate with limited pending cases.

news.title: Illegal colonies, kiosks set up for plot sales & boundary walls razed in Gurugram
news.para: Gurugram's DTCP is actively demolishing unauthorized constructions across the city, targeting illegal colonies and structures in areas like Palam Vihar and Carterpuri. Authorities are also addressing the misuse of power by RWAs, who are carrying out illegal constructions in group housing societies. The potential appointment of administrators is being considered for RWAs repeatedly violating norms.

news.title: Pune civic body tells developers to display project names in Marathi
news.para: Pune Municipal Corporation has mandated developers to display names of residential and commercial projects in Marathi. This follows a demand from Maharashtra Navnirman Sena. PMC commissioner Naval Kishore Ram issued a circular regarding this. MNS wants the administration to monitor the implementation. Building permissions granted by PMC have increased significantly over the past few years.

news.title: Ghaziabad: GDA to fast-track new township in Indirapuram amid property price surge
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority will speed up work on the Indirapuram Extension project. This decision follows a sharp increase in property values and housing demand. The project, planned across 230 acres, faced delays due to land acquisition issues. Now, with a detailed layout plan in progress, the township development is set to move forward.

news.title: Over 1.36 lakh houses constructed under PMAY-Urban in Odisha in 10 years: Data
news.para: Odisha government achieved a milestone. It completed 1.36 lakh houses for the urban poor under PMAY-U since 2015. The Odisha Urban Housing Mission provided the data. The government sanctioned 1.84 lakh houses. 73% of the target is complete. Beneficiaries received financial assistance of Rs 2 lakh. This helped them construct new houses with basic amenities.

news.title: Arisinfra Solutions' profit down 21% to ₹5 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Arisinfra Solutions Ltd reported a 21% decline in net profit to Rs 5.11 crore for Q1 FY26, attributed to IPO-related expenses, despite a rise in total income to Rs 215.6 crore. Excluding these expenses, profit after tax would have exceeded the entire FY25 figure.

news.title: The Ramco Cements' profit rises to ₹181.58 crore in Q1 FY26
news.para: Ramco Cements announces a consolidated net profit of Rupees 181.58 crore for the June quarter. This is due to improved cement prices and operational efficiencies. Revenue slightly decreased to Rupees 2,074 crore. Cement sales volume saw a 7% decline because of weak demand and early monsoons. The company plans to reach a cement capacity of 30 MTPA by March 2026.

news.title: JSW Cement IPO booked 56% on day 2 of offer
news.para: JSW Cement's IPO saw 56% subscription on its second day, with strong retail and non-institutional investor interest. The IPO includes a fresh issue and an offer-for-sale by existing shareholders like Apollo Management and SBI. Proceeds will fund a new cement unit in Rajasthan and debt repayment, valuing the company at Rs 20,000 crore.

news.title: DLF to invest ₹23,500 crore to complete ongoing housing projects in NCR, Mumbai
news.para: India's DLF will invest significantly to finish ongoing housing projects in Delhi-NCR and Mumbai. The company possesses substantial cash reserves and receivables from sold properties. DLF invested in construction during the first quarter and anticipates increased spending. Recent project launches in Mumbai and Gurugram witnessed complete sell-outs.

news.title: HSBC takes extra space in Canary Wharf due to HQ squeeze
news.para: HSBC has leased additional office space at 40 Bank Street in Canary Wharf due to insufficient room at its future headquarters near St Paul's Cathedral. This decision provides a boost to Canary Wharf, which has faced declining office values and planned departures.

news.title: Tesla India takes on lease 8,200 sq ft commercial space in Delhi's Aerocity
news.para: Tesla is expanding its Indian footprint, leasing 8,200 sq ft of commercial space in Delhi's Aerocity for Rs 17.22 lakh monthly, with a 9-year lease and rent increases every three years.

news.title: Varmora Granito files IPO papers with Sebi, eyes ₹400 crore via fresh issue
news.para: Varmora Granito Ltd, a tiles and bathware manufacturer, has filed for an IPO with Sebi to raise funds through a fresh issue of shares worth Rs 400 crore and an OFS of 5.24 crore equity shares. The company intends to use the proceeds to repay borrowings and for general corporate purposes.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers, subsidiaries exit stakes in four entities
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers has reorganised its portfolio. The company's subsidiary, Kolte-Patil Lifespaces, has exited Amco Landmarks Realty for ₹4 crore. Kolte-Patil and its subsidiaries have also exited Kolte-Patil Realtors Estate, Regenesis Project Management LLP, and Ayaan Vihan Land Development.

news.title: Info Edge (India)'s net profit up 32.45% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Info Edge (India) announced a 32.45% increase in net consolidated profit for Q1 FY26, reaching ₹342.85 crore, with total income rising by 21.28% to ₹1,004.07 crore. Despite macroeconomic uncertainties, the company demonstrated steady growth and improved earnings per share.

news.title: Grasim Industries' net profit increases by 33.94% in Q1 FY26
news.para: Grasim Industries witnessed a 33.94% surge in net consolidated profit, reaching ₹2,767.08 crore in Q1 FY26, fueled by a 15.89% rise in total income to ₹40,460.18 crore. The building materials segment, driven by Cement, Paints, and B2B E-commerce, saw a 22% revenue growth.

news.title: Indian REITs cross ₹one lakh crore in market capitalisation
news.para: Indian REITs are performing well. The combined market value of the four listed REITs crossed ₹one lakh crore on July 30, 2025. These REITs manage significant assets. They operate over 128 million sq ft of office and retail space. They have distributed over ₹22,800 crore to investors since inception. The sector is experiencing strong leasing and occupancy.

news.title: DRA & Balajadia Family office create $100 million platform to develop commercial spaces
news.para: DRA Group and Balajadia Family Office have partnered to form a 50:50 joint venture, investing $100 million to develop one million sq ft of grade-A commercial and retail space in Chennai and Bengaluru. This collaboration aims to combine local expertise with global capital for sustainable real estate growth in India. Future collaborations may bring Indian expertise to the Philippines.
